The Archives of Virology is a peer-reviewed scientific journal covering research in virology. It is published by Springer Science+Business Media and is the official journal of the Virology Division of the International Union of Microbiological Societies. It was established in 1939 as the Archiv f√ºr die gesamte Virusforschung and obtained its current title in 1975. According to the Journal Citation Reports, the journal has a 2011 impact factor of 2.111.
